reviews.author: Julio Augusto Trujillo Espinoza
reviews.text: A parish, linked to the history of Comas. Sixty years ago, when the invasions occurred in the Km. 13 sector, the first settlers, needing land to live on, took possession of this area, which they called Villa Señor de los Milagros, using their faith as their only shield and banner, the Face of the Lord. This face is venerated to this day in the Señor de los Milagros Parish of Comas, Km. 13. Many of the first settlers were arrested and imprisoned, but their persistence had the desired effect: they had land to live on. When they began to subdivide the land, they demarcated the area where the Señor de los Milagros Parish would be built. In its early years, it was managed by the Congregation of the Oblates of Mary Immaculate. The people write their history, and we are merely the actors.

name: Chapel of Our Lady of the Precious Blood

reviews.author: Néstor René Mayma Quispe
reviews.text:
Our Lady of the Precious Blood Chapel: One of the most representative chapels in our neighborhood, which over time has become one of the most recognized religious centers in the area.
To receive services, please contact the Nuestra Señora de la Luz Chapel office, next to the Santa Luzmila market. From this contact, you can request a religious ceremony for this chapel in El Retablo.
Located next to the Ramón Castilla Elementary School and two blocks from the El Retablo Metro Hypermarket.
